30/01/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX has launched a preliminary investigation into allegations of human organ trafficking cited in CoE rapporteur Dick Marty's report, a spokesperson for the mission said Friday (January 28th).
The mission takes these allegations "very seriously" but will not launch any prosecutions unless there are facts and evidence, the spokesperson, Karin Limdal, said in a statement.
(Blic, B92 - 29/01/11;
AP, BBC - 28/01/11)
